news.title: Gurugram: Gaps in rainwater harvesting system, nine builders served notices
news.para: The developers of these projects, most of which are in the new sectors, have been asked to submit compliance reports by September 19 with pictorial evidence of providing pits to residents’ welfare associations (RWAs) for the system and cleaning of existing harvesting structures.

news.title: MahaRERA sets up citizens' call centre to resolve queries of homebuyers
news.para: MahaRERA secretary Vasant Prabhu said the helpdesk was initiated, as many citizens had expressed their inability to reach out to the authorities In the wake of the pandemic for various queries.

news.title: SC seeks status report from ED, police on probe against Unitech, ex-promoters
news.para: Both Sanjay and Ajay who are in jail since August 2017 are accused of allegedly siphoning home buyers' money. The top court in its October 2017 order had asked them to deposit Rs 750 crore with the apex court registry by December 31, 2017.

news.title: Goa government seeks time till November 30 to finalise coastal plan
news.para: Nilesh Cabral had earlier said that Goa is planning to seek sn extension by only one month, but he said on Tuesday that the state wants to seek three months’ time as a precaution to ensure the deadline is met this time.

news.title: Fitch downgrades China Evergrande, flags 'probable' default
news.para: Regulators have warned that Evergrande's 1.97 trillion yuan ($304.79 billion) of liabilities could spark broader risks to the country's financial system if not stabilised.

news.title: Thiruvananthapuram civic body to compile & submit files requiring CRZ clearance
news.para: The town planning adalat which began here on Tuesday received around 14 applications for which CRZ clearance was mandatory for issuing building permit.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers elevates Yashvardhan Patil as Joint MD, Rahul Talele as group CEO
news.para: Rahul Talele, currently Business Head- Pune, has been appointed as the company's Group CEO with effect from September 08, 2021, the company said in a regulatory filing.

news.title: Jaipur: JDA in soup over 'illegal' luxury hotel construction at Rambagh Circle
news.para: As per documents in possession of TOI, the influential hotelier is allegedly carrying out new construction and extending the hotel in violation of JDA norms.

news.title: Adjudicate floor-wise sale dispute in two weeks: SC to Punjab & Haryana HC
news.para: The SC passed these directions on Monday and a copy was made available on Tuesday. Earlier, the apex court had stayed the directions of the high court related to survey of estate office properties, where there has been transfer of shares.

news.title: Kalyan-Dombivli civic body chief orders inquiry as builder accuses officials of taking bribe
news.para: Builder Munna Singh has submitted CCTV footage from the hotel as evidence to KDMC commissioner Dr Vijay Suryawanshi, where the civic officials had come to meet him to take the money, and demanded action against them.

news.title: About 1.5 lakh patta applications disposed of every month: Tamil Nadu govt tells HC
news.para: As per the status report submitted by the commissioner of survey and settlement, the number of applications pending for disposal as on October 1 2020, was 5,76,771.

news.title: Panchkula civic body issue sealing notices to 10 property owners over unpaid tax
news.para: Mayor Kulbhushan Goyal said during the meeting of the Revenue and Realisation Committee, it was decided to take strict action against property tax defaulters to supplement MC revenue and carry out developmental works.

news.title: Chandigarh: Small flats handed over in 2015; CHB yet to get 21.64 acres of land
news.para: ​The flats were constructed on 21.64 acres of CHB land, which was transferred to UT urban planning department for the ambitious Union government project. However, UT has not given equivalent land to the board despite several reminders and letters.

news.title: Unique ID code a must to register East Delhi properties
news.para: After the civic body approached Delhi government to incorporate UPIC among the documents required for registration to bring all property details online, an order was issued by the government to implement the proposal on a pilot basis.

news.title: Rajasthan: 400 applications under PMAY rejected citing landline telephone connections
news.para: A local NGO has challenged the report of the local administration by stating that 90% of families are living in shanties and don’t have a power connection, let alone landline phones.
